        <p><lb n="1"/>saṁvaT <num value="386"><g type="numeral">300</g><g type="numeral">80</g> 6</num> jyaiṣṭha-māse śukla-pakṣe pratipadi <num value="1">1</num>
<lb n="2"/><supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->ro</supplied>hiṇī-nakṣattra-yukte candramasi muhūrtte praśaste bhijiti<!-- 
L1. saṁvaT: I tend to insert halanta consonants for Gnoli's final consonants before numerals or daṇḍas and at the end of lines; these are mere guesses. 
--></p>
        <lg met="śārdūlavikrīḍita" n="1">
          <l n="a"><lb n="3"/><supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->śrī</supplied>vatsāṅkita-dīpta-cāru-vipu<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->la</supplied>-prodvr̥tta-vakṣa<supplied reason="omitted">ḥ</supplied>-sthalaḥ</l>
          <l n="b"><lb n="4"/><supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->śrī</supplied>-vakṣaḥ-stana-padma-bāhu-<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->vima</supplied>laḥ samyak-pravr̥ddhotsavaḥ</l>
          <!-- 
v1b. (Footnotes in these inscr. from Nepal mostly copied from Gnoli.)
śrī is "Conjectural reading. Bh.I. and L. omit this syllable".
vimala: "L., Bh.I.: °(ruciraḥ); the syllabe la is clearly visible".
pravr̥ddhotsavaḥ: conjectural reading; L.: sma-pravr̥ddhotsavaḥ; Bh.I.: sma<supplied reason="undefined">rttr̥</supplied>pravr̥ddhotsavaḥ 
-->
          <l n="c"><lb n="5"/><supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->trai</supplied>lokya-bhrama-yantra-vartti <seg met="--+">
              <gap quantity="3" reason="lost" unit="character"/>
            </seg> vyāsaṅga-nityo <supplied reason="subaudible">’</supplied>vyayaḥ</l>
          <!-- 
v1c. L.; Bh.I.: °yantrava- 
-->
          <l n="d"><lb n="6"/><supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->do</supplied>lādrau nivasañ jayaty ani<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->mi</supplied>ṣair abhyarccyamāno hariḥ</l>
          <!-- 
v1d.  Bh.I.: abhyarcyamāno (without duplicating the c). The consonants which follow the r are always duplicated, with the exception of the bh of bhāryyā°, II, line 1, and the d of dr̥ḍham, II, line 15 
-->
        </lg>
        <lg met="śārdūlavikrīḍita" n="2">
          <l n="a"><lb n="7"/><seg met="++">
              <gap quantity="2" reason="lost" unit="character"/>
            </seg> tsā <seg met="--">
              <gap quantity="2" reason="lost" unit="character"/>
            </seg> ya-pratāpa-vibha<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->vair vvyā</supplied>yāma-saṁkṣepa-kr̥t</l>
          <l n="b"><lb n="8"/><supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->rājābhū</supplied>d vr̥ṣadeva Ity <supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->anupamaḥ sa</supplied>tya-pratijñodayaḥ</l>
          <l n="c"><lb n="9"/><seg met="+++">
              <gap quantity="3" reason="lost" unit="character"/>
            </seg> saviteva dīpta-kira<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->ṇaiḥ</supplied> samyag-vr̥<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->taḥ</supplied> svaiḥ sutaiḥ</l>
          <!-- 
v2c. = = = : Yogī Naraharinātha (S.S., I, 6, p. 40) has <supplied reason="undefined">yo reje</supplied>.
vr̥taḥ: Bh.I. and L. read and integrate dr̥<supplied reason="undefined">taiḥ</supplied>. The conjecture vr̥<supplied reason="undefined">taḥ</supplied> has been kindly suggested to me by B. Ch. Chhabra 
-->
          <l n="d"><lb n="10"/>vidvadbhir bbahu-garvvitair aca<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->palaiḥ</supplied> <seg met="++">
              <gap quantity="2" reason="lost" unit="character"/>
            </seg> vinītātmabhiḥ</l>
          <!-- 
v2d. = = : The integrations khyātair (Bh.I ) or śūrair (Yogī Naraharinātha, op. cit.) are both plausible. Sometimes the consonants which follow the r are not duplicated (cf. n. 6, above) 
-->
        </lg>
        <lg met="śārdūlavikrīḍita" n="3">
          <l n="a"><lb n="11"/><supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->ta</supplied>syābhūt taṇayaḥ samr̥ddha-<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->viṣa</supplied>yaḥ saṁkhyeṣv ajeyo <supplied reason="subaudible">’</supplied>ribhiḥ</l>
          <!-- 
v3a. taṇayaḥ sic in ed. 
-->
          <l n="b"><lb n="12"/><supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->bhūpa</supplied>ḥ śaṅkaradeva Ity apa <seg met="-++">
              <gap quantity="3" reason="lost" unit="character"/>
            </seg> ti-pradaḥ satya-dhīḥ</l>
          <!-- 
v3b. bhūpaḥ: Read; Bh.I. and L. have <supplied reason="undefined">rājā</supplied> 
-->
          <l n="c"><lb n="13"/><seg met="+">
              <gap quantity="1" reason="lost" unit="character"/>
            </seg> yā-vikrama-dāna-māna-vi<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->bhavai</supplied>r llabdhvā yaśaḥ puṣkalaM</l>
          <!-- 
v3c. the ed. actually prints  = . here. Dot is for part of akṣara missing. 
-->
          <l n="d"><lb n="14"/><seg met="+++-">
              <gap quantity="4" reason="lost" unit="character"/>
            </seg> rarakṣa gām abhi<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->matair bbhr̥</supplied>tyai<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->r mmr̥ge</supplied>ndropamaḥ</l>
          <!-- 
v3d. Bh.I. and L. omit to duplicate the bh and the m after the r 
-->
        </lg>
        <lg met="śārdūlavikrīḍita" n="4">
          <l n="a"><lb n="15"/><supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->tasyā</supplied>pi Uttama-dharmma-karmma-ya <seg met="-+++-">
              <gap quantity="5" reason="lost" unit="character"/>
            </seg> vid dhārmmikaḥ</l>
          <!-- 
v4a. BhJ. does not duplicate the m.
CHECK CsK: It should read tasyāpy (metre). 
-->
          <l n="b"><lb n="16"/><supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->dha</supplied>rmmā<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->tmā</supplied> vinayepsur utta<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->ma-guṇaḥ śrī-dha</supplied>rmmadevo nr̥paḥ</l>
          <l n="c"><lb n="17"/><supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->dha</supplied>rmmeṇaiva kula-kramāgata <seg met="-+++-">
              <gap quantity="5" reason="lost" unit="character"/>
            </seg> rājyaṁ mahaT</l>
          <l n="d"><lb n="18"/>s<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->phī</supplied>tī-kr̥tya nayair nnr̥pa-rṣi-cari<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->taiḥ saṁ</supplied>bhāvya ceto nr̥nāM</l>
          <!-- 
v4d. taiḥ saṁ : "I propose" ed.; Bh.I., L.: °cari = = bhāvya 
-->
        </lg>
        <lg met="śārdūlavikrīḍita" n="5">
          <l n="a"><lb n="19"/><supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->re</supplied>je sa <seg met="-">
              <gap quantity="1" reason="lost" unit="character"/>
            </seg> śubhiḥ surānu <seg met="--+">
              <gap quantity="3" reason="lost" unit="character"/>
            </seg> ḥ sampanna-mantra-rddhibhiḥ</l>
          <!-- 
v5a. The conjectural reading of L., sa<supplied reason="undefined">ttvāṁ</supplied>śubhiḥ, cannot be upheld, because the metre reguires a short syllable instead of <supplied reason="undefined">ttvāṁ</supplied> 
-->
          <l n="b"><lb n="20"/><seg met="+">
              <gap quantity="1" reason="lost" unit="character"/>
            </seg> māvā <seg met="-">
              <gap quantity="1" reason="lost" unit="character"/>
            </seg> viśuddha-deha-hr̥dayaś candra-dyutiḥ pārtthivaḥ</l>
          <!-- 
v5b. CHECK Phps " = māyā" in ed.? 
-->
          <l n="c"><lb n="21"/><supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->pa</supplied>tnī tasya viśuddha-vaṁśa-vibhavā śrī-rājyavaty uttamā</l>
          <l n="d"><lb n="22"/><supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->prā</supplied>ṇā<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->nām a</supplied>bhavat <supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->priyā</supplied> kula-gu<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->ṇai</supplied>r llakṣmīr iv<supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->ā</supplied>gryā hareḥ</l>
          <!-- 
v5c. prāṇānām from corrigenda. 
-->
          <!-- 
v5d. "I owe the restoring of this verse to Yogī Naraharinātha, op. cit. L. has = ṇā = . bhavat = kulaśu = r 
-->
        </lg>
        <lg met="śārdūlavikrīḍita" n="6">
          <l n="a"><lb n="23"/><seg met="+++-">
              <gap quantity="4" reason="lost" unit="character"/>
            </seg> rater yyaśoṁśubhir idam <supplied reason="lost"><!-- CHECK if <unclear> applies better.-->v</supplied>yābhāsya kr̥tsnañ jagat</l>
          <l n="b"><lb n="24"/>yāti sma tri-divālayan nara-patāv udyāna-yātrām iva</l>
          <l n="c"><lb n="25"/>pramlānā jvara-vihvalā kula-ja <seg met="++">
              <gap quantity="2" reason="lost" unit="character"/>
            </seg> neka-mandā tadā</l>
          <l n="d"><lb n="26"/>devāhāra-vidhi-kriyāsv abhiratā tad-viprayogāt purā</l>
        </lg>
